- Peptides are short chains of amino acids that can bind to MHC molecules;
- MHC stands for Major Histocompatibility Complex, which is a group of proteins on the surface of cells that present peptides to TCRs;
- The confidence score is a measure of the likelihood that a TCR-peptide-MHC interaction is biologically significant, with higher scores indicating greater confidence.

